one|WPC-108|6}} ({{navy|USA|coast guard}}) and {{USS|Hamilton|DMS-18|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}). ''Byron D. Benson'' sank on 8 April.<ref name=BDB>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/1503.html |title=Byron D. Benson |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=6 April 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Catahoula||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United States|1912}}\n|desc=World War II: The tanker was torpedoed and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean ({{coord|19|16|N|68|12|W}}) by {{GS|U-154|1941|2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of seven of her 45 crew. Survivors were rescued by {{USS|Sturtevant|DD-240|6}} ({{navy|United States|1912}}).<ref name=Catahoula>{{cite web |url=http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/1502.html |title=Catahoula |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=29 February 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMS|Cornwall|56|6}} \n|flag={{navy|United Kingdom}}\n|desc=[[File:HMS Cornwall - 1942 - WWII.jpg|thumb|HMS ''Cornwall'']]\nWorld War II: [[Easter Sunday Raid]]: The {{sclass2-|County|cruiser}} was bombed and sunk in the [[Indian Ocean]] {{convert|200|nmi|km}} south west of [[Ceylon]] by Japanese aircraft with the loss of 198 of her 700 crew.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Dardanus||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and damaged in the [[Bay of Bengal]]   by [[Nakajima B5N]] aircraft based on {{ship|Japanese aircraft carrier|Ry\u016bj\u014d||2}}. Taken under tow by {{SS|Gandara||2}} ({{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}). Shelled and sunk the next day by {{ship|Japanese cruiser|Mikuma||2}} and {{ship|Japanese cruiser|Mogami|1934|2}} (both {{navy|Empire of Japan}}).<ref name=\"Imperial cruisers\">{{cite web |url=http://www.combinedfleet.com/Mogami_t.htm |title=Imperial cruisers |publisher=Combinedfleet.com |accessdate=6 April 2014}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMS|Dorsetshire|40|6}} \n|flag={{navy|United Kingdom}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Easter Sunday Raid]]: The {{sclass2-|County|cruiser}} was bombed and sunk in the Indian Ocean {{convert|200|nmi|km}} south west of Ceylon by Japanese aircraft with the loss of 234 of her 653 crew.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{MV|Empire Beacon||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The coaster struck a [[naval mine|mine]] and sank in the [[Bristol Channel]] off St. Anns Head, [[Pembrokeshire]]\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Feddy||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=The cargo ship was lost in a collision with the trawler ''Visenda'' ({{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}) off [[North Ronaldsay]].<ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=1127452|shipname=Feddy |accessdate=4 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMS|Gallant|H59|6}} \n|flag={{navy|United Kingdom}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[G and H-class destroyer|G-class]] [[destroyer]] was bombed and damaged beyond economical repair while being repaired after having previously lost her bow to a mine and being beached at [[Malta]] on 10 January 1941. The wreck was refloated and sunk as a blockship in September, 1943.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uboat.net/allies/warships/ship/4391.html |title=HMS Gallant (H59) of the Royal Navy |publisher=U Boat.net |accessdate=5 April 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Harpasa||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk in the [[Bay of Bengal]]  by \"Kate\"s  from {{ship|Japanese aircraft carrier|Ry\u016bj\u014d||2}}. 6 crewmen killed.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.combinedfleet.com/Ryujo_t.htm |title=Imperial Flattops |publisher=Combinedfleet.com |accessdate=6 April 2014}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMS|Hector|F45|6}} \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Easter Sunday Raid]]: The [[armed merchantman|armed merchant cruiser]] was bombed and sunk at [[Colombo]], Ceylon by Japanese aircraft.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Ninetto G.||2}} \n|flag={{Flagcountry|Kingdom of Italy|