outh.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/warships/ship/6411.html |title=Anti-submarine Trawler HMS Lord Snowden|publisher=Uboat |accessdate=13 April 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|PiLB 210||2}}  \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The PiLB 40 type landing craft was lost on this date.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_pilb40.htm |title=PiBL 40 type landing craft, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=6 April 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Soviet motor sailer|Partizan Zheleznay||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=World War II: The motor sailer was sunk by mines in the [[Kerch Gulf]]. Her [[Sea captain|Master]] and five crewmen were killed.<ref name=\"Shipnostalgia.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.shipsnostalgia.com/guides/Soviet_Merchant_Marine_Losses_in_WW2_%28Black_Sea%29|title=Soviet Marine Losses in WWII (Black Sea) |publisher=Shipnostalgia.com |accessdate=13 April 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Ryujin Maru||2}} \n|flag={{Flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Pacific Ocean]] south west of [[Shikoku]] by {{USS|Grayling|SS-209|6}} ({{navy|United States}}).<ref name=Grayling>{{cite DANFS |title=Grayling |url= http://www.hazegray.org/danfs/submar/ss209.txt |accessdate=31 December 2011 }}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==14 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=14 April 1942 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Anton Chekov||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The [[transport ship]] struck a [[naval mine|mine]] and sank in the [[Black Sea]] off [[Kerch]]. There were 200 killed and 50 wounded.<ref name=seekrieg194204/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kchf.ru/ship/vspomog/anton_chehov.htm |title=Chekov |publisher=www.kchf.ru |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://cmboat.ru/vov14-04-1942/ |title=Chekov 