p|Soviet patrol boat|No. 102||2}}  \n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[MO-class small guard ship#MO-4 type|''MO-4''-class]] [[patrol vessel]]  was lost on this date.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/russia/ru_cf_mo4.htm |title=MO-class small guard ship, USSR |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=25 April 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{MV|Patella|1927|2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[tank ship|tanker]] was shelled and sunk by {{ship|German auxiliary cruiser|Michel||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}). 5 crewmen were killed, 60 were taken as [[prisoners of war]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.wrecksite.eu/wreck.aspx?137127 |title=Patella Tanker 1927-1942 |publisher=Wrecksite |accessdate=30 November 2014}}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==20 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=20 April 1942 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{MV|Agra||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Sweden}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean {{convert|280|nmi|km}} north west of [[Bermuda]] ({{coord|34|40|N|69|35|W}}) by {{GS|U-654||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of six of her 39 crew. Survivors were rescued by {{MV|Tercero||2}} ({{flag|Norway}}).<ref name=Agra>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/1551.html |title=Agra |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=15 April 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Arete|1928|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Sweden}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[coastal trading vessel|coaster]] struck a [[naval mine|mine]] and sank in the [[Great Belt]] with the loss of four lives.<ref name=seekrieg194204/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.konditori100.se/SiWW2/sww2lscs.htm |title=Swedish WWII losses |publisher=www.konditori100.se |accessdate=21 October 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMS|Cotswold|L54|6}} \n|flag={{navy|United Kingdom}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Convoy FS 80]]: The {{sclass2-|Hunt|destroyer}} struck a mi